Part1

Class DoubleNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • Part1.DoubleNode

  • public class DoubleNode
extends java.lang.Object
    The class DoubleNode holds two node references and a character. An instance of this class is a single node on a DoublyLinkedList
    Author:
    nkhani@andrew.cmu.edu

    • Constructor Detail

      • DoubleNode

        public DoubleNode()
        Default constructor for DoubleNode class no-arg constructor. Assigns null to the prev, next and a null character to data

      • DoubleNode

        public DoubleNode(char c)
        Constructor to create a node only from the char data. This comes in handy when the prev and next references are uncertain just yet in the program
        Parameters:
        c - char data to be held in the node of the list postcondition Creates a new instance of DoubleNode which stands alone carrying on the char data. prev and next are set to null automatically

      • DoubleNode

        public DoubleNode(DoubleNode p,
                  char ch,
                  DoubleNode n)
        Constructor for the DoubleNode class. Used to create a new DoubleNode object. Note the parameters required here.
        Parameters:
        p - - Reference to the previous node in the list. This is null if the node is the head node.
        n - - Reference to the next node in the list. This is null if the node is tail node or last node.
        ch - - This is the char data that each node holds. precondition ch should be a valid char data postcondition a new instance of the DoubleNode is created No-Case : Big Theta (1)

      • getPrev

        public DoubleNode getPrev()
        This is a getter method to access the previous node in the list.
        Returns:
        Returns a reference pointing to the previous node in the list. Note: If this method is called on the head of the list, a null is returned.
